================================================================
PRACTICAL NO. 8 - EVENTS, SCREEN SCRAPING & PLUGINS IN UIPATH
================================================================

PRE-REQUISITES:
- UiPath Studio installed
- Chrome browser with UiPath Extension installed
  (In UiPath Studio → Tools → UiPath Browser Extension → Install for Chrome)
- UiPath packages: UiPath.UIAutomation.Activities, UiPath.Mail.Activities,
  UiPath.PDF.Activities (install via Manage Packages)

================================================================
PRACTICAL 8(a) - Demonstrate Triggering Events in UiPath
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Medium-Hard

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will demonstrate three types of event triggers:
  (i)  Element Triggering Event (Click Trigger)
  (ii) Image Triggering Event
  (iii) System Triggering Event (Hotkey Trigger, Mouse Trigger)

NOTE: Trigger activities run CONTINUOUSLY in the background and wait 
for an event. They are used inside a "Monitor Events" or 
"Trigger Scope" activity. The workflow pauses and waits 
for the trigger to fire.

--- (i) ELEMENT TRIGGERING EVENT - CLICK TRIGGER ---

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_8a_Events

Step 2: Open Notepad on your computer.

Step 3: In the sequence, drag a "Monitor Events" activity.
  (If not found, search in Activities panel — it may be in UI Automation section)

Step 4: Inside Monitor Events, in the EVENT HANDLER section,
        drag a "Click Trigger" activity.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - Click on the Notepad text area.
  - This means: "Watch for a click on Notepad's text area."

Step 5: In the ACTION section of Monitor Events,
        drag a "Message Box" activity.
  - Text: "You clicked on Notepad!"

Step 6: Run (F5).
  - UiPath waits in the background.
  - Click on the Notepad text area.
  - The Message Box should pop up immediately.

Step 7: Press Stop in UiPath to end the monitoring.

--- (ii) IMAGE TRIGGERING EVENT ---

Step 8: For Image Trigger, you need a reference screenshot.
  - Take a screenshot of any visible button or icon on screen.
  - Example: take a screenshot of Notepad's "Format" menu text.

Step 9: Inside a new Monitor Events activity, drag an "Image Found Trigger".
  - Click "Indicate image on screen"
  - Draw a rectangle around the element/image you want to detect
    (e.g., the word "Format" in Notepad's menu bar).
  - UiPath will watch for this image to appear.

Step 10: In the Action section, drag a "Message Box".
  - Text: "Target image was detected on screen!"

Step 11: Run (F5).
  - UiPath waits.
  - If that image appears on screen, the message box fires.

--- (iii) SYSTEM TRIGGERING EVENTS ---

HOTKEY TRIGGER:

Step 12: Inside a new Monitor Events activity, drag a "Hotkey Trigger".
  - Key: F10 (or any key you like)
  - Modifier: None (or Ctrl, Alt, Shift — your choice)
  - This watches for when you press that key.

Step 13: In the Action section, drag a "Message Box".
  - Text: "Hotkey was pressed!"

Step 14: Run (F5) → Press F10 → Message Box appears.

MOUSE TRIGGER:

Step 15: Inside a new Monitor Events, drag a "Mouse Trigger".
  - MouseButton: Left (watch for left mouse button)
  - InputEvent: Click
  - This fires when anywhere on the screen is clicked.

Step 16: In Action section, drag a Message Box.
  - Text: "Mouse click detected!"

Step 17: Run (F5) → click anywhere → Message Box fires.

